<div class="station">Putbus</div>
<div class="desc">
	Putbus is a small town on the island of Ruegen with about 4,000 residents. The
	Putbus train station is located in the center of the town and is served by the
	Ruegensche Kleinbahn, a narrow-gauge railway that connects Putbus with Binz,
	Goehren, and Lauterbach. The station building is a listed building and was
	built in 1899.
